response:
 Since 5 and 7 are both prime, $5^{23}$ and $7^{17}$ are both odd. The sum of two odd numbers is even, i.e., divisible by 2. Moreover, $5^{23}$ and $7^{17}$ end with 1, thus the their sum ends with 2 and is divisible by 10.
They are also divisible by 3 because
\begin{align*}
5^{23} &= (3+2)^{23} \\
&\equiv 2^{23} \pmod{3}
\end{align*}
which is negative since $2^5 = 32 \equiv -1 \pmod{3}$. Therefore $5^{23} + 7^{17}$ is divisible by 2, 5, and 3. The smallest is $\boxed{3}$.
