\end{align*}
for all $x\in \mathbb{R}$ and hence
\begin{align*}f(x)^2-2x^2 &=1
\end{align*}
for all $x\in \mathbb{R},$ so that
\begin{align*}f(x)&= \pm\sqrt{1 + 2x^2}
\end{align*}
for all $x\in \mathbb{R}.$ Now, evaluating $(\alpha)$ at $(-n,n)$ and using
\begin{align*}f(n)^2-2n^2=f(n-n)^2-2n^2=-4n^2\end{align*}
for all $n\in\{1,2,\ldots,2019\},$ we see that $f(n)=-f(-n)$ for all $n\in\{1,2,\ldots,2019\},$ so that
